      <p class="sl gt mb-3">Common Questions</p>
      <h2 style="font-family:'Barlow Condensed',sans-serif;font-weight:800;font-size:clamp(2rem,4vw,3rem);line-height:.95;color:#1A1A1A;letter-spacing:-.01em">TARPON SPRINGS ROOFING FAQ</h2>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <button class="faq-btn" aria-expanded="false" onclick="this.setAttribute('aria-expanded',this.getAttribute('aria-expanded')==='true'?'false':'true');this.nextElementSibling.classList.toggle('open')">
        How much does a roof replacement cost in Tarpon Springs?
        <svg width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#1A1A1A" stroke-width="2.5"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6"/></svg>
      </button>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        <div class="faq-answer-inner">Roof replacement costs in Tarpon Springs typically range from $8,000 to $25,000+ depending on your roof's size, pitch, material choice (shingles, metal, or tile), and whether structural repairs are needed. Homes near the Sponge Docks and in the historic district may require special attention due to older construction methods and Mediterranean architectural details. Happy Roof provides free, detailed estimates with no hidden fees — call <a href="tel:8135957663" class="call-tracking-number" style="color:#3B9FD9;text-decoration:none;font-weight:600">(813) 595-7663</a> for a personalized quote.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <button class="faq-btn" aria-expanded="false" onclick="this.setAttribute('aria-expanded',this.getAttribute('aria-expanded')==='true'?'false':'true');this.nextElementSibling.classList.toggle('open')">
        What roofing materials are best for homes near the Tarpon Springs coast?
        <svg width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#1A1A1A" stroke-width="2.5"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6"/></svg>
      </button>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        <div class="faq-answer-inner">Tarpon Springs homes near the Gulf coast, Anclote Key, and Sunset Beach face salt air corrosion, intense UV exposure, and hurricane-force winds. Standing seam metal roofing with galvalume or aluminum panels resists salt corrosion and lasts 40–60 years. Owens Corning Duration HDZ shingles rated for 130+ MPH winds are an excellent choice for inland neighborhoods like Holiday and Elfers. Tile roofs complement the Greek-influenced architecture throughout the historic district and remain one of the most durable options for coastal Florida homes.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <button class="faq-btn" aria-expanded="false" onclick="this.setAttribute('aria-expanded',this.getAttribute('aria-expanded')==='true'?'false':'true');this.nextElementSibling.classList.toggle('open')">
