      <button class="faq-btn" aria-expanded="false" onclick="this.setAttribute('aria-expanded',this.getAttribute('aria-expanded')==='true'?'false':'true');this.nextElementSibling.classList.toggle('open')">
        How long does a roof replacement take in Tarpon Springs?
        <svg width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#1A1A1A" stroke-width="2.5"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6"/></svg>
      </button>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        <div class="faq-answer-inner">Most Tarpon Springs shingle roof replacements are completed in 1 to 3 days. Metal roofs typically take 3 to 5 days, and tile roofs may require 5 to 7 days depending on complexity and the specific tile profile. Florida's summer afternoon thunderstorms can occasionally cause brief delays, but we plan around weather and keep you updated at every stage of the project.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <button class="faq-btn" aria-expanded="false" onclick="this.setAttribute('aria-expanded',this.getAttribute('aria-expanded')==='true'?'false':'true');this.nextElementSibling.classList.toggle('open')">
        Is Happy Roof licensed to work in Tarpon Springs?
        <svg width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#1A1A1A" stroke-width="2.5"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6"/></svg>
      </button>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        <div class="faq-answer-inner">Yes. Happy Roof LLC holds Florida Roofing Contractor License #CCC1337380, which authorizes roofing work throughout the entire state of Florida — including the City of Tarpon Springs and all of Pinellas County. We carry full general liability and workers' compensation insurance, and certificates are available upon request.</div>
      </div>
